### REST Client Requests for Rateio API
### Use the REST Client extension (humao.rest-client) in VS Code
### Click "Send Request" above each request to execute it

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@apiUrl = {{baseUrl}}/api

### Variables (update these with your actual values)
@txid = abc123def456...
@rateioId = c8de05ad-e01e-4205-ab9c-589aa0f647c8
@participantId = aa8532c9-3782-4de9-8466-2e3fcf7df19c

###############################################
# EFÍ PAY WEBHOOK TEST ENDPOINTS
###############################################

### Find txid from Participant ID
GET {{apiUrl}}/webhook/efipay/find-charge/{{participantId}}

### Simulate Payment - Manual (Webhook Simulation)
### Use this for quick local testing without calling Efí API
### NOTE: "amount" is OPTIONAL and in CENTS (e.g., 1000 = R$ 10.00)
### If not provided, uses the participant's contribution amount
POST {{apiUrl}}/webhook/efipay/test
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "participantId": "{{participantId}}"
}

### Simulate Payment with Custom Amount (in cents)
POST {{apiUrl}}/webhook/efipay/test
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "participantId": "{{participantId}}",
  "amount": 1000
}

### Pay QR Code via API - Official (Homologation Test)
### This calls the real Efí Pay API to pay the QR Code
### Requires: pix.send and gn.qrcodes.pay scopes enabled
### Homologation key: [email protected]
POST {{apiUrl}}/webhook/efipay/pay-qrcode
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "participantId": "{{participantId}}",
  "payerPixKey": "[email protected]"
}

### Simulate Payment - Using txid (legacy)
POST {{apiUrl}}/webhook/efipay/test
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "txid": "{{txid}}",
  "amount": 300
}

###############################################
# RATEIO ENDPOINTS (tRPC)
###############################################

### Get Rateio by ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/trpc/rateio.getById
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "json": {
    "id": "{{rateioId}}"
  }
}

### Get Rateios by Creator
POST {{baseUrl}}/trpc/rateio.getByCreator
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "json": {}
}

### Get Participants by Rateio
POST {{baseUrl}}/trpc/participant.getByRateio
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "json": {
    "rateioId": "{{rateioId}}"
  }
}

### Get Participant by ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/trpc/participant.getById
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "json": {
    "id": "{{participantId}}"
  }
}

###############################################
# PAYMENT ENDPOINTS (tRPC)
###############################################

### Create Payment Intent (Gerar QR Code Pix)
POST {{baseUrl}}/trpc/payment.createIntent
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "json": {
    "participantId": "{{participantId}}",
    "amount": 300
  }
}

### Get Payment Status
POST {{baseUrl}}/trpc/payment.getStatus
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "json": {
    "participantId": "{{participantId}}"
  }
}

### Transfer to Creator (Enviar Pix para o criador)
### Requires authentication (session cookie)
POST {{baseUrl}}/trpc/payment.transferToCreator
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "json": {
    "rateioId": "{{rateioId}}"
  }
}

###############################################
# NOTES
###############################################

### How to use:
### 1. Install REST Client extension in VS Code
### 2. Update variables at the top with your actual values
### 3. Click "Send Request" above any request to execute it
### 
### For Efí Pay, configure these environment variables:
### - EFI_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id
### - EFI_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret
### - EFI_CERTIFICATE_PATH=./path/to/certificate.p12
### - EFI_SANDBOX=true (use false for production)
### - EFI_PIX_KEY=your_pix_key
###
### The webhook test endpoint bypasses mTLS validation
### and allows simulating payments for testing purposes.
###
### Key differences from Pagar.me:
### - Uses txid instead of chargeId
### - Requires mTLS certificate for API calls
### - Uses OAuth2 token-based authentication
### - Can send Pix directly to any Pix key (transferToCreator)

